# IriScale Lead Generation Strategy: Scorecard Marketing Funnel

> **Source Video:** [The $1 Million Landing Page (Works For Normal People)](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=az1Zh-FNSno) by Daniel Priestley  
> **Strategy Type:** Assessment / Scorecard-Based Lead Generation (aka "Scorecard Marketing")  
> **Tool Referenced in Video:** [ScoreApp](https://www.scoreapp.com/) (Priestley is co-founder)  
> **IriScale Feature Reference:** `iriscale _app_assessment/` folder  
> **Transcript Source:** Full YouTube transcript  
> **Date Created:** February 12, 2026

---

## Part 1: Video Strategy Breakdown (from Full Transcript)

### Core Thesis

> "If there is one thing that I've learned over the last 20 years of scaling multiple companies, it's this: **Everything is downstream from lead generation.** If you can generate leads, you can solve all the other problems after that. But if you cannot generate leads, you are dead in the water."

Daniel Priestley describes a **multi-million dollar lead generation system** that he sets up every single time he takes on a new business project. He has used it on: **agencies, software companies, education and training, coaching, consulting**, and other businesses. The system is an **online assessment** that generates leads consistently.

### The System: 4 Parts

---

#### Part 1: Landing Page (0:48)

The landing page explains what the assessment will do for people. It has 5 components in order:

**1. The Hook (top of page — first thing people see on their phone)**

Choose ONE of two hook types:

- **Frustration Hook:** Names the frustration people are experiencing. Formula: *"Feeling frustrated that [problem] even though [you're already doing X]."*
  - Example: "Feeling frustrated that you're not getting the fitness results you want even though you work out every week"
  - Example: "Feeling frustrated that you're not getting investment returns even though you invest consistently every month"
  - Example: "Feeling frustrated that you have not been able to scale up your marketing even though you're willing to invest in ads"

- **Results Hook (Readiness Sentence):** Asks if they're ready for a specific result. Formula: *"Are you ready to [desired result]?"*
  - Example: "Are you ready to run your first marathon?"
  - Example: "Are you ready to have the relationship of your dreams?"
  - Example: "Are you ready to protect your business from a cyber security threat?"
  - Why it works: People think "I'm not sure if I'm ready — I want to take this assessment to find out."

**2. Subheading**

Directs people to take the assessment. Formula: *"Answer 15 questions to find out why you're experiencing this frustration and what to do about it."*

**3. Value Proposition**

Tell people the assessment will **measure and improve 3 key areas**. Formula: *"Take this assessment so we can measure and improve [Area 1], [Area 2], and [Area 3]."*

- Example (sleep assessment): "Answer these 15 questions so we can measure and improve your sleep environment, your sleep routine, and your sleep nutrition."
- The 3 areas should be things people would love to achieve on the way to the bigger result.

**4. Credibility Section**

People hear a powerful hook + value proposition and immediately wonder if it's credible. This section answers:
- **Who created this?** — Your name and bio
- **What have you done in the past?** — Your background
- **What research have you done?** — Statistics, figures, studies
  - Example: "85% of people struggle with X, Y, and Z"
  - Example: "A recent Harvard University study found that 15% of people are achieving X"

**5. Call to Action (CTA)**

Must cover these 4 elements:
1. **Start the quiz** — that's the next step
2. **It only takes 3 minutes** to complete
3. **It's completely free**
4. **You get immediate recommendations** on how you can improve

**Key Metric from Priestley:** If you get this right, **20-40% of people who hit the landing page will start the quiz.** That is a massive lead generator.

---

#### Part 2: Questionnaire — 15 Questions in 3 Parts (4:17)

**Part A — Contact Information (required to start the quiz):**

| Field | Required? | Notes |
|-------|-----------|-------|
| Name | Yes | Must enter to start |
| Email | Yes | Must enter to start |
| Location | Auto-captured | Via IP address |
| Phone number | Optional | Give them the opportunity but don't make it mandatory |

**Part B — 10 Best Practice Questions (these generate the score):**

Ask people if they're doing 10 things they should be doing. These are yes/no or scaled multiple-choice questions about best practices in the relevant domain. The answers directly determine their score.

Priestley's examples:
- Sleep assessment: "Do you get to bed at the same time every night?" "Are you using too many screens before bed?"
- Fitness assessment: "Do you track your calories?" "Do you work out three or four times a week?"

> You need to come up with 10 best practices that you think people should be doing if they're doing all the right things. That's what informs the score.

**Part C — 5 Qualifying Questions (these qualify the lead for sales):**

| # | Question | Format | What It Reveals |
|---|----------|--------|-----------------|
| **Q1** | "Which best describes your current situation?" | Multiple choice (4-5 options) | Where they are right now. Examples: "I'm a student / first 5 years of career / manager / senior leader / executive" or "Never run a marathon / run 1-3 / seasoned runner" |
| **Q2** | "Which describes your desired outcome you'd like to achieve in the next 90 days?" | Select from list | The #1 thing driving their decisions. Examples: "I want to lose weight" / "I want to achieve my first 7 hours of deep sleep" |
| **Q3** | "What is the obstacle you think is stopping you? Or what have you tried that hasn't worked?" | Multiple choice (3-4 options) | Their biggest perceived obstacle to success |
| **Q4** | "Which solution do you think would suit you best?" | Multiple choice | **Implies budget.** Examples: "I want education and training / one-to-one coaching / software / someone to do it all for me." A book buyer = $10-$20. "Do it all for me" = $10,000-$20,000 |
| **Q5** | "Is there anything else you think we need to know about?" | Open text box | Incredibly valuable. People write things like: "I've already read your book and want to get started" or "I have a budget but have to spend it by end of the month" |

> Priestley notes: If they've answered all 14 other questions, they're going to give you really good relevant information in this open box too.

---

#### Part 3: Dynamic Results (8:19)

Called "dynamic" because the entire results page **changes depending on how they answered the questions.** Three components:

**1. The Big Reveal — Overall Result**

Visual indicator of their performance:
- Speedometer showing "You got 75% out of 100%"
- Thermometer showing cold / warm / hot
- Dynamic text: "Congratulations, you scored really well" OR "Oh no, you've got a lot of room to improve" OR "Well done, you've got strong foundations but plenty of room to improve"

**2. Three Insights**

Based on how they answered, present 3 things you want them to know. These change per respondent.

**3. Next Steps (tiered by qualification)**

| Lead Quality | Recommended Next Step |
|-------------|----------------------|
| **Highly qualified** | Offer a one-to-one meeting |
| **Middle of the road** | Offer a group presentation or group event |
| **Wrong for your business** | Give them content — send to a video, podcast episode, or recommend a book |

**Bottom of results page:** All contact information, social media links, website link — so people can bounce around to other pages.

---

#### Part 4: Dashboard & Traffic (10:34)

**The Dashboard captures everything:**
- How people answered all questions
- How they scored
- Where they are (location)
- Whether they put in real contact information
- The recommended next step
- All laid out in one view

**The Tool — ScoreApp:**
- Priestley is co-founder of scoreapp.com
- 150 templates based on this strategy
- Free downloadable book: *Scorecard Marketing*
- Online courses explaining the system
- Customer success team for setup help
- Most people set up in 10-30 minutes

**Traffic (mentioned briefly — separate video):**
- Common question: "How do I send people to this landing page?"
- He references a separate video: [How To Get Noticed](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=WiTIgjYxWbE)
- That video covers paid + organic traffic, starting small and scaling big
- **This is a gap in the current video** — traffic strategy is not covered here

