## Part 2: How IriScale Can Utilize This Strategy

### Why This Is a Strong Fit for IriScale

1. **IriScale is a SaaS platform** — Priestley specifically lists software companies as a proven use case for this system
2. **IriScale has 17 distinct features** across 5 suites — the assessment can help prospects self-identify which features solve their problems and segment themselves by readiness
3. **IriScale already has a TOFU/MOFU/BOFU framework** (Topic Strategy) — the assessment naturally sits as a BOFU conversion tool with supporting content feeding into it
4. **IriScale can "eat its own cooking"** — use IriScale's own features (Keyword Repository, Content Architecture, Social Posts, Opportunity Agent) to drive traffic to the assessment

### Proposed Assessment: "The AI Content Marketing Scorecard"

---

#### Landing Page — Applied to IriScale

**Frustration Hook Options:**

| Hook | Formula Applied |
|------|----------------|
| Option A | "Feeling frustrated that your content isn't generating leads even though you're publishing consistently?" |
| Option B | "Feeling frustrated that your competitors are showing up in AI search results even though you've invested in SEO?" |
| Option C | "Feeling frustrated that you can't scale content production even though you're willing to invest in tools?" |

**Results Hook Options:**

| Hook | Formula Applied |
|------|----------------|
| Option A | "Are you ready to have AI handle your content marketing from research to publishing?" |
| Option B | "Are you ready to show up when customers ask ChatGPT, Perplexity, or Claude about your industry?" |
| Option C | "Are you ready to turn your content into a consistent lead generation engine?" |

**Subheading:** "Answer 15 questions to find out where your content marketing is falling short and get a personalized action plan to fix it."

**Value Proposition — 3 Key Areas to Measure and Improve:**

| Area | What We Measure | IriScale Features That Solve It |
|------|-----------------|--------------------------------|
| **1. AI Search Visibility** | Are you showing up when people ask AI assistants about your industry? | Search Ranking Intelligence, AI Optimization Questions, AI Optimization Answers |
| **2. Content Strategy & Production** | Do you have a structured plan and the ability to produce content at scale? | Knowledge Base, Keyword Repository, Content Architecture, Topic Strategy, Articles |
| **3. Social Presence & Opportunity Capture** | Are you actively finding and engaging prospects where they're talking? | Opportunity Agent, Social Posts, Social Scheduler, Connections |

**Credibility Section:**

- IriScale platform: 5 suites, 17+ features, AI-powered across the entire content lifecycle
- Tracks visibility across 5 AI search platforms simultaneously (ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, Grok)
- AI-generated competitive intelligence including sales battle cards
- Cite customer results/metrics when available (TBD — need real data)

**CTA:** "Start the quiz. It only takes 3 minutes. It's completely free. Get immediate recommendations on how you can improve."

**Expected conversion:** 20-40% of landing page visitors start the quiz (Priestley's benchmark).

---

#### Questionnaire — Applied to IriScale

**Part A — Contact Info:**

| Field | Required? | IriScale-Specific Note |
|-------|-----------|------------------------|
| Name | Yes | |
| Email | Yes | |
| Location | Auto (IP) | Useful for regional targeting |
| Company name | Yes (add this) | Helps personalize follow-up |
| Company website URL | Yes (add this) | Could be auto-ingested into IriScale Knowledge Base for personalized demo |
| Phone number | Optional | |

**Part B — 10 Best Practice Questions (generate the score):**

These ask if they're doing 10 things they should be doing for effective AI-powered content marketing. Each maps to an IriScale capability:

| # | Best Practice Question | Best Answer (what "yes" looks like) | IriScale Feature |
|---|----------------------|-------------------------------------|------------------|
| 1 | Do you have a centralized knowledge base that all your content is generated from? | Yes — single source of truth for all content | Knowledge Base |
| 2 | Do you actively research and manage keywords with volume, competition, and intent data? | Yes — with AI-powered research | Keyword Repository |
| 3 | Do you track how your company appears in AI search results (ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, Gemini, Grok)? | Yes — across all major AI platforms | Search Ranking Intelligence |
| 4 | Do you have documented, regularly updated competitive intelligence on your key competitors? | Yes — automated and comprehensive | Competitor Analysis |
| 5 | Do you have a structured content architecture (page hierarchy) for your website? | Yes — AI-planned with SEO settings | Content Architecture |
| 6 | Do you know what questions your customers are asking AI assistants about your industry? | Yes — and we create optimized answers | AI Optimization Questions |
| 7 | Can you generate on-brand blog articles at scale with quality control? | Yes — AI-generated with human review | Articles |
| 8 | Do you monitor social platforms (Reddit, etc.) for real-time sales opportunities in your space? | Yes — automated monitoring and alerts | Opportunity Agent |
| 9 | Do you have documented brand voice and writing guidelines that all content follows? | Yes — auto-generated and enforced | Brand Voice & Writing Guidelines |
| 10 | Can you create and schedule social content across multiple platforms from one place? | Yes — 7 platforms with campaign management | Social Posts + Scheduler |

> Scoring: Each "yes" or strong answer adds points. Score out of 100% based on how many best practices they follow.

**Part C — 5 Qualifying Questions (qualify the lead):**

| # | Question | Options | What It Reveals for Sales |
|---|----------|---------|---------------------------|
| **Q1** | Which best describes your current content marketing situation? | (a) Just getting started — no real system yet (b) We create content but it's ad hoc and inconsistent (c) We have a system but it's plateauing / not scaling (d) We have a mature operation but want to add AI automation | Maturity / readiness level |
| **Q2** | What is the #1 outcome you want to achieve in the next 90 days? | (a) Increase organic search traffic (b) Show up in AI search results (c) Scale content production without adding headcount (d) Get better competitive intelligence (e) Automate social media management (f) Build a content-to-lead pipeline | Primary motivation — maps directly to IriScale features |
| **Q3** | What's the biggest obstacle stopping you? | (a) We don't have the right tools (b) Our team is too small (c) We don't know where to start with AI (d) Budget constraints (e) Content quality concerns (f) We've tried tools before and they didn't work | Pain point — informs sales approach |
| **Q4** | Which solution would suit you best? | (a) Self-serve software platform I can learn myself (b) Software with guided onboarding and support (c) A fully managed service — do it all for me (d) Training and education first, then tools (e) Not sure yet — need to learn more | **Budget signal.** Self-serve = lower tier. Managed service = premium. "Not sure" = needs nurture |
| **Q5** | Is there anything else about your content marketing challenges we should know? | Open text box | Gold mine. People share timelines, budgets, specific frustrations, prior tool experience |

