#### Promotion & Traffic — Using IriScale's Own Features

| IriScale Feature | How It Drives Assessment Traffic |
|-----------------|----------------------------------|
| **Keyword Repository** | Research high-volume keywords: "AI content marketing tools," "content marketing assessment," "AI SEO platform," "how to show up in AI search results" — use for paid ads and organic targeting |
| **AI Optimization Questions** | Discover what prospects are asking AI assistants about content marketing → generate answers that include CTA to take the assessment |
| **Content Architecture** | Build a content hub with supporting pages: "What is AI content marketing?", "How to audit your content strategy," "AI search visibility guide" — all linking to the assessment |
| **Topic Strategy** | Generate full-funnel topics: TOFU ("What is AI SEO?") → MOFU ("How to choose a content marketing platform") → BOFU (the assessment itself) |
| **Articles** | AI-generate supporting blog articles for each topic, targeting assessment-related keywords |
| **Social Posts + Scheduler** | Create and schedule promotional content for the assessment across 7 platforms. Campaign intent: "Promote" with KPI: "CTR" or "Conversions" |
| **Opportunity Agent** | Set up agents monitoring Reddit for discussions about content marketing tools, AI SEO, content scaling challenges → engage with link to assessment |
| **Competitor Analysis** | Use battle card data to sharpen assessment positioning vs. competitors (e.g., "unlike [Competitor], IriScale covers the full content lifecycle") |

